<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="I" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Irish" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Irish,</orth> pertaining to Ireland: <cit><quote>I was an I. rat,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 3.2.188" default="NO" valid="yes">As III, 2, 188</bibl></cit> (rats were supposed to be killed by certain mystic rhymes). <cit><quote>I. wolves,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 5.2.119" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 119</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>I. wars,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 1.4.62" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 I, 4, 62</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. r2 2.1.155" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 155</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 2.1.155" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 155</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.3.150" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 3, 150</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 4.3.88" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 88</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 5.1.53" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 53</bibl>. Substantively, == Irish language: <cit><quote>howl in I.</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 3.1.241" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A III, 1, 241</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>